<br>
*He has already used VX/nerve agent in his own homeland. <br>
*Looking at the nuclear half life of radiated material and contamination, coupled with nuclear fall out that will travel the globe, I don't see how anything could be worse then nuke. One exception would be smallpox, which has the high probability of exterminating a large portion of the planets  population.<br>
*Something to be considered is that for chem/ bio to be effective it's &quot;persistancy&quot; must be considered. In most cases, vectors for bio (rats, insects etc). Blister, blood, choking and nerve agents depend heavily on weather and terrain. <br>
<br>
 It's interesting that Iraq is probably the worst enviornment to attempt to use these to the maximum of success. Perhaps not known to all is the fact that Iraq is not entirely open desert (not the likes of Saudi/ Kuwait). However, with the lack of abundant vectors and the possibility of world wide epidemic/ outbreak, to include his own population and more importantly his army, I don't think he would use bio. <br>
<br>
 Considering the intense direct sunlight, high winds and loose/ migrant topsoil chem weapons would have a minimum long term impact. This would work in his favor to reduce an immediate military threat, while lessening the chance of permantly polluting his country. I believe he's more likely to go with VX/ nerve, through artillery shells/ rockets whatever (which he's pretty much got down to a science).<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;And clearly Saddam aint gonna attack first and loose whatever international support/symphaty he has.&quot; - Kwaij<br>
<br>
 I must entirely agree with you here. The concern that I and many of my countrymen have is that these weapons will be distributed intentionally or unintenionally to people that would use them against us without hesitation. <br>
<br>
 Crossing the border and smuggling these out would be no difficult accomplishment in Iraq. The bedouin don't recognize borders in the Mid-east and this region, crossing them daily without inspection (among others).<br>
<br>
 If Saddam wasn't playing a game of three card monty with his WMD/ &quot;now you see them, now you dont&quot;, our country wouldn't have issue. No one can deny that he's hiding them, and I really can't understand why this doesn't alarm the international community. <br>
<br>
 I can say with almost 100% surety that these WMD will not turn up among the French population. I'm not banging the French persay, just pointing out the fact there's really only one country I feel at risk atm. <br>
